The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for image segmentation, specifically for cardiac MR images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also explores various neural network architectures and modifications, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of MR images also suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for segmentation suggests the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
